  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ambiguous requirement)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The governing requirement is stated in terms of 'adequate predictive fidelity' and 'clinically acceptable hemolysis performance', language whose compliance threshold depends on an uncited internal guidance document.",
